  "texts": [
    "The typical wave patterns and the bubble's main characteristic structure are marked out in the figures.",
    "For example, \"TS\" represents the transmitted shock propagating downstream inside the bubble, which is generated after the incident shock impacts the bubble.",
    "The shock focusing occurs when two high-pressure regions meet, which in turn produces secondary transmitted shock waves (STS), Reflected Rarefaction Waves (RRW), and jet.",
    "These typical wave patterns during the SBI can all be captured by DBM.",
    "The evolution of bubble characteristic scales during the SBI process are demonstrated in Fig. 28."
